## 15. PRE-LAUNCH SECURITY & PRIVACY CHECKLIST

Items that MUST be addressed before public launch. Track against this list before announcing Koy publicly.

### Authentication & Account Security
- [ ] **Email verification turned ON** in Supabase Dashboard → Authentication → Settings. Currently OFF, allowing fake account creation. Spam risk at scale.
- [ ] **Password reset flow tested end-to-end.** Supabase has it built-in but verify the "forgot password" link is wired to the auth modal and emails are deliverable.
- [ ] **Account deletion exposed in Account Settings page.** Currently no UI to delete account. GDPR requirement if launching in EU; basic respect regardless. `cascade` deletes through pages/comments/calendar_entries; `set null` on user_events anonymizes data.
- [ ] **OAuth providers wired** (Google + Apple) — currently email+password only. Sprint 9+ scope but flag for launch readiness.

### Rate Limiting & Abuse Prevention
- [ ] **Verify Supabase rate limits** are configured. Free tier has defaults; check Settings → API. Anon key is exposed in client bundle (normal for client apps), so rate limiting is the only defense against script abuse.
- [ ] **Add rate limit on user_events writes** — even with the auth.uid() = user_id policy, an authenticated user can spam millions of events to inflate their own activity or pollute the AI-training-data table. Options: trigger limiting inserts per user per minute, OR Edge Function with rate limit. Critical before selling data to any AI buyer.
- [ ] **Add rate limit on comments** — max 5 per user per minute. Currently no limit; comment-spam is the easiest abuse vector at launch scale.

### Content Safety
- [ ] **Comment moderation: report button.** Add "report this comment" → stores report → manual review queue (acceptable at first 1-5K users; automated tooling like Hive/Sightengine when reports exceed ~20/day).
- [ ] **Comment moderation: simple word blocklist** for the worst content. Free, fast, blocks obvious abuse.
- [ ] **DMCA takedown procedure documented.** Required to use Section 512 safe harbor protection. Email address (e.g., dmca@koy.app), response SLA, takedown form.
- [ ] **Image upload moderation.** User-uploaded images are highest-risk content vector. NSFW/copyrighted/etc. Either manual review queue at v1 OR moderation API (Hive, Sightengine, Cloudflare). Budget $100-500/month at small scale.

### Data Privacy
- [ ] **Privacy Policy published.** Cannot legally collect user data without one. Cover what data is collected, how it's used (especially the user_events → AI training story), retention, deletion.
- [ ] **Terms of Service published.** Cover acceptable use, IP ownership, content removal rights, account termination, liability limits.
- [ ] **Cookie consent banner** if launching in EU/UK markets.
- [ ] **Document the public-storage caveat.** User-uploaded images live at guessable URLs in `user-uploads` bucket (path: `{user_id}/{block_id}/{timestamp}-{filename}`). If user removes an image from a page, the URL still works for anyone who saved it. True of all public CDNs (Imgur, Cloudinary, etc.) but document in Privacy Policy.

### Architectural Security
- [ ] **CSRF concern flagged for OAuth migration.** Currently JWT in headers (not cookies), so CSRF mitigated. When OAuth lands (Sprint 9+), reassess if cookie-based auth is introduced.
- [ ] **Audit log for sensitive changes** — currently no record when users change email, handle, password. Standard at scale; build before significant adoption.

### Pre-Launch Sign-Off
Cannot announce public launch until all critical items (email verification, Privacy Policy, ToS, account deletion, password reset, comment report button, rate limits) are complete. The "non-negotiable" items above are the minimum legal and ethical floor.

