## 16. ARCHITECTURAL HEALTH & PLANNED REFACTORS

Track these planned refactors so they don't get forgotten. None are urgent but all become problems if deferred indefinitely.

### State Management Refactor (Target: Sprint 4)

**Current:** App.jsx manages all state via useState at the top, drilled down through props. Pattern works at current scale but produces stale-closure bugs (the 6d color picker bug was this) and prop-drilling depth grows with every feature.

**Trigger to act:** Sprint 4 (package architecture) adds `userPackages`, `editorTheme`, `editorOpacity`, `customCursorUrl` as new state. Prop drilling becomes unmanageable.

**Plan:** Introduce single `useAppState()` hook with `useReducer` and React Context. Lightweight — no Redux, no Zustand. Just one Context provider at App root, hooks consume what they need.

**Scope when done:**
- One reducer in `src/hooks/useAppState.js`
- Context provider wraps `<App />`
- Components call `const { entries, upsertEntry } = useAppState()` instead of receiving props
- Eliminates ~80% of current prop drilling
- Fixes stale-closure bugs by design

### File Split Refactor (Target: Sprint 3 or 4)

**Current:** Single `src/App.jsx` file holds everything. Estimated 3,000+ lines. Manageable today but every sprint adds 2-3 components and the file is becoming a monolith.

**Trigger to act:** When App.jsx hits ~5,000 lines OR when adding a feature requires touching more than 6 different sections of the file.

**Planned split:**
```
src/
  App.jsx                     — routes + top-level state only
  Editor.jsx                  — editor mode logic
  PublicPage.jsx              — read-only public view
  Account.jsx                 — settings page
  components/
    CellEditor.jsx
    ImgEdit.jsx
    BSheet.jsx
    Cal.jsx
    [other extracted components]
  lib/
    supabase.js              — all DB calls
    storage.js               — upload helpers
    auth.js                  — auth helpers
  hooks/
    useIsMobile.js
    useAppState.js           — central state if Context approach
```

### Repeated Logic Extraction (Ongoing)

Watch for the "rule of three" — when a pattern appears in three different components, extract it into a shared utility. Current candidates being monitored:

- **Mobile vs desktop render branches.** Each new feature has two render paths. Eventually need a `<ResponsiveContainer mobileSlot desktopSlot />` pattern or similar.
- **Save state machines.** Yellow → green → red status dot transitions are needed for comments, pages, calendar entries, image uploads. If reimplemented per-feature, extract.
- **Authentication checks.** "Is user logged in?" "Is user the page owner?" "Is user premium?" — should be 2-3 helper functions at most.

